x4freetext: ENERGY SPECTRA AND ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION OF
PHOTONEUTRONS FROM OXYGEN.

x4freetext: THE TARGET WAS ABOUT ONE MOLE OF BIDISTILLED WATER
CONTAINED IN A THIN GUM VESSEL WHOSE WEIGHT WAS
ONLY 0.15 G.
. ONLY THOSE TRACKS, ORIGINATED AND COMING TO REST
IN THE EMULSION, AND WITH A `DIP` ANGLE < 15 DEGREES
AND AN `AZIMUTH` ANGLE < 30 DEGREES INTO A PYRAMID
CENTERED IN THE NEUTRON BEAM DIRECTION, HAVE BEEN
CONSIDERED.
. 400 MU THICK ILFORD L-4 EMULSION.
DUE TO A) THE PROBABILITY OF ESCAPE OF THE TRACKS
FROM THE EMULSION, B) THE ABSORPTION AND SCATTERING
OF NEUTRONS IN THE WATER TARGET, C) THE BACKGROUND.
. THE CORRECTION DUE TO ABSORPTION AND SCAT-
TERING OF NEUTRONS IN THE WATER TARGET WAS CALCULATED.
. SOME LEVELS OF O-16 WERE FOUND.
THE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS WERE FITTED BY LINEAR
COMBINATION OF LEGENDRE POLYNOMIALS.
THE NEUTRON SPECTRA SHOW A FINE STRUCTURE IN GOOD
AGREEMENT WITH THE FINE STRUCTURE FOUND IN THE PROTON
SPECTRA AND IN THE (G,N) AND (G,P) CROSS SECTIONS.
FROM THESE STRUCTURES MANY LEVELS OF THE O-16 NUCLEUS
ARE IDENTIFIED WHICH ARE IN GOOD AGREEMENT WITH KNOWN
LEVELS AND SOME LEVELS GIVEN WITH UNCERTAINTY ARE
CONFIRMED.
FOR THE O-16(G,N) REACTION THE CONTRIBUTION OF
DIRECT PROCESS APPEARS PREVALENT WHILE FOR ALL
ELEMENTS UP TO THESE DATA INVESTIGATED EVAPORATION
ACCOUNTS FOR THE GREATER PART OF EMITTED NEUTRONS.
THE GROUND STATE TRANSITIONS AMOUNT TO AT LEAST
60% OF THE EMITTED NEUTRONS.
A BACK AND FRONT ASYMMETRY OF THE ANGULAR
DISTRIBUTIONS OF PHOTONEUTRONS FOR SINGLE NEUTRONS
PEAKS IS FOUND IN THE REGION OF THE GIANT RESONANCE.
. DATA WERE COMPILED IN SCJAD OF SARATOV STATE
UNIVERSITY.
CORRECTED BY V.VARLAMOV, V.MCLANE

x4freetext: . THE GROUND STATE.
ONLY A LOWER PART OF THE SPECTRA (E < 5 MEV) MAY
CONTAIN A NON NEGLIGIBLE PERCENTAGE OF NEUTRONS
THAT LEAVE O-15 IN EXCITED STATES.
THE CALCULATION TAKING INTO ACCOUNT THE IRRADIATION
DOSE, THE BREMSSTRAHLUNG SPECTRUM AND THE ENERGY
SPECTRA OF PHOTONEUTRONS FOR VARIOUS ANGLES WAS MADE
BY MEANS OF SPECIAL FORMULA TO OBTAIN THE CROSS
SECTION FOR PHOTOABSORPTION GIVING RISE TO TRANSI-
TIONS TO THE GROUND STATE OF O-15.
STATISTICAL ERRORS ARE PRESENTED.
1) THE CROSS SECTION CALCULATION IS SUFFICIENTLY
CORRECT FOR E > 5 MEV AND HENCE FOR E-GAMMA > 21 MEV,
WHILE IT GIVES A SUPERVALUATION FOR E-GAMMA < 21 MEV.
2) THE POSITION OF THE PEAKS MARKED BY FLAG IN
THE CROSS SECTION FOR O-16(G,N) REACTION AND IN
THE CROSS SECTION OF O(G,P) PROCESS TO THE GROUND
STATE OF N-15. THEY ALSO AGREE WITH THE SAME POSITIONS
IN THE ENERGY SPECTRUM OF PHOTONEUTRONS (SEE SUBENT
